This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an algorithm for solving machine learning problems. It may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as it deals with optimization algorithms. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it discusses a method suitable for big data problems. It may also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as ADMM is commonly used in network optimization problems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as ADMM is used in image processing and computer vision applications.
